name.text: Solving a Quadratic Inequality and Factorizing

questiontext.text:
The goal of this question is to solve the following quadratic inequality \({@quest@} > 0\).


(a) Factorise \( {@quest@}\).

[[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]]

[[feedback:prt5]]


(b) Now solve the inequality.

[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] or [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]

[[feedback:prt2]]

generalfeedback.text:
Worked solution

(a) To factorize the quadratic expression, we need to find two numbers that multiply to give {@c0@} and sum to {@c1@}.
These are {@-a1@} and {@-b1@}, so the solution is:

\({@quest@} = {@ta1_ta2@}\)


(b)The solution to the inequality \({@ta1_ta2@} >0\) is {@ta3@} or {@ta4@}.

Here is the graph that corresponds to the quadratic inequality. Note that the solution to the inequality is the region (highlighted in red) where the graph is above the \(x\)-axis.

{@plot( [ ta1_ta2, [discrete,[[a1 -5,0],[a1,0]]], [discrete,[[a1 -5,0.1],[a1,0.1]]], [discrete,[[a1 -5,-0.1],[a1,-0.1]]], [discrete,[[b1,0],[b1 +5,0]]], [discrete,[[b1,0.1],[b1 +5,0.1]]], [discrete,[[b1,-0.1],[b1 +5,-0.1]]] ], [x,a1 -5,b1 +5], [box, false], [yx_ratio, 1], [xtics, a1 -5, 1, b1 + 5], grid2d, [color,blue,red,red,red,red,red,red] )@}
